Model Fully Visible

[

](https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/the-rules/core-rules/#Model-Fully-Visible)

If every part of another model that is facing the observing model can be seen from any part of the observing model, then that other model is said to be fully visible to the observing model, i.e. the observing model has line of sight to all parts of the other model that are facing it, without any other models or [terrain features](https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/the-rules/core-rules/#Terrain-Features) blocking visibility to any of those parts.  
  

![](Core%20Rules_files/DeterminingVisibility3.webp)

HOVER

Some aircraft can use vectored thrusters or anti-grav technology to hover over the battlefield, the better to hunt their prey or deploy embarked troops.

Some [AIRCRAFT](https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/the-rules/core-rules/#Aircraft) models have ‘Hover’ listed in their abilities. When you are instructed to [Declare Battle Formations](https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/the-rules/core-rules/#Declare-Battle-Formations), before doing anything else, you must first declare which models from your army with this ability will be in Hover mode.  
  
If a model is in Hover mode, then until the end of the battle, its Move characteristic is changed to 20", it loses the AIRCRAFT keyword and it loses all associated rules for being an AIRCRAFT model. Models in Hover mode do not start the battle in [Reserves](https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/the-rules/core-rules/#2.-Reinforcements), but you can choose to place them into [Strategic Reserves](https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/the-rules/core-rules/#Strategic-Reserves) following the normal rules if you wish.

